rcli
------------------------------------------
rcli is a powerful C++ library that simplifies the creation of CLI
applications. It provides convenient user input functions and efficiently
manages command-line options and subcommands.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.4-1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  librcli-devel-2.0.23-1bl1
  librcli2-2.0.23-1bl1
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.45-1
  cmake-3.28.3-1
  cygport-0.37.2-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/RickaPrincy/rcli

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/RickaPrincy/rcli/archive/refs/tags/v2.0.23.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack rcli-2.0.23-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./rcli-2.0.23-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/rcli-2.0.23-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/rcli-2.0.23-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/librcli2-2.0.23-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/librcli-devel-2.0.23-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(rcli)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/rcli.README
  /usr/share/doc/rcli/License.txt
  /usr/share/doc/rcli/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/rcli/images/command.png
  /usr/share/doc/rcli/images/default_color.png
  /usr/share/doc/rcli/images/version.png

(librcli2)
  /usr/bin/cygrcli-2.dll

(librcli-devel)
  /usr/include/rcli/app.hpp
  /usr/include/rcli/command.hpp
  /usr/include/rcli/option.hpp
  /usr/include/rcli/rcli.hpp
  /usr/include/rcli/rcli_config.hpp
  /usr/lib/cmake/rcli/rcliConfig.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/rcli/rcliTargets-release.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/rcli/rcliTargets.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/rcli/rcliVersion.cmake
  /usr/lib/librcli.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/rcli.pc

